# VAIC — environment layout (pointer only)
#
# There is intentionally NO root .env anymore. Env is split by consumer so each
# variable has a single source of truth and nothing is duplicated:
#
#   infra/.env      -> docker-compose (Postgres/Redis).  Template: infra/.env.example
#   backend/.env    -> FastAPI app + arq worker (VAIC_*). Template: backend/.env.example
#   frontend/.env   -> Vite dev server (VITE_*).          Template: frontend/.env.example
#
# Setup:
#   cp infra/.env.example    infra/.env
#   cp backend/.env.example  backend/.env
#   cp frontend/.env.example frontend/.env
#
# Start infra (reads infra/.env explicitly):
#   docker compose --env-file infra/.env -f infra/docker-compose.yml up -d
#
# If you change POSTGRES_PORT / REDIS_PORT in infra/.env, update the matching
# host/port in backend/.env (VAIC_DATABASE_URL, VAIC_DATABASE_ADMIN_URL,
# VAIC_REDIS_URL) so the app connects to the right ports.
#
# Never commit any real .env (NFR-6).
